	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=34280><span id=Scholar>Teanne</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>47 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.55]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Thats not actually true.&nbsp;&nbsp;At higher dual wield skills, you hands become independant of each other.<br><br>However, you are right about wanting really low delay in your primary hand.  Remember how great the moss covered twig was?  3/10 Is a terrible ratio, but it was uber because of how low the delay is on it.  You get a fixed damage bonus on every swing, and a lower delay weapon can and will net you more damage than a better ratio but slower weapon.<br><br>6/13 is a decent ratio for 1hb, and a fantastic delay, making this a very good weapon.  So good that it should drop off of something tough like Vulak so it doesnt get nerfed like the twig did.<br><br>BTW, just to finish the lesson about dual wielding, you want the best possible ratio in your offhand because you dont get a damage bonus on that hand.<br><br>Teanne Tranquilshowers<br>Disciple of Quellious<br>Tunare Server</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
